ZH: 我们应该珍惜每一分钱财。
EN: We should cherish every penny of money.
ZH: 钱财并不是万能的，但缺乏却会让人倍感痛苦。
EN: Money is not everything, but the lack of it can make people feel miserable.
ZH: 他总是把钱财看得比亲人更重要。
EN: He always values money more than his own family.
ZH: 钱财能买到物质享受，但不能买到幸福。
EN: Money can buy material pleasures, but not happiness.
ZH: 我宁愿拥有健康的身体，也不愿追求腰包里的钱财。
EN: I would rather have a healthy body than chase after money in my wallet.
ZH: 这份工作的好处不仅仅是为了钱财。
EN: The benefits of this job are not just for money.
ZH: 他从不在钱财方面浪费时间。
EN: He never wastes time when it comes to money.
ZH: 对于钱财的管理，他信心满满。
EN: He is confident in managing money.
ZH: 她真的是一个擅长理财的人，钱财总是井井有条。
EN: She is really good at managing money, and everything is in order.
ZH: 他的人生哲学是“钱财并不是万能的”。
EN: His life philosophy is "money is not everything."
ZH: 钱财只是代表一种物质财富，但不代表一个人的内在价值。
EN: Money represents material wealth, but not a person's intrinsic value.
ZH: 她把钱财当做追求幸福的手段，而不是终极目的。
EN: She sees money as a means to pursue happiness, not the ultimate goal.
ZH: 如果对于钱财的追求让你失去了自己，那就不值得了。
EN: If the pursuit of money makes you lose yourself, it's not worth it.
ZH: 钱财能让人拥有自由，但也可能让人变得越来越贪婪。
EN: Money can give people freedom, but it can also make people more and more greedy.
ZH: 他不在乎钱财，只在乎家人的幸福。
EN: He does not care about money, only his family's happiness.
ZH: 钱财很重要，但健康更重要。
EN: Money is important, but health is more important.
ZH: 对他来说，钱财永远都是次要的。
EN: For him, money is always secondary.
ZH: 我们应该学会正确管理自己的钱财。
EN: We should learn to manage our money properly.
